          <title>Jimmy Carter, the 39th US president, has died at 100</title>
          <description><![CDATA[ATLANTA (AP) — Jimmy Carter, the peanut farmer who won the presidency in the wake of the Watergate scandal and Vietnam War, endured humbling defeat after one tumultuous term and then redefined life after the White House as a global humanitarian, has died. He was 100 years old.]]></description>
